A. Boulanger excavated at Aphrodisias, principally in the area of the Hadrianic Baths; see A. Boulanger, Notes sur les fouilles executées en 1913 à Aphrodisias, Comptes rendus des séances de l’année de l’Académie des inscriptions et belles-lettres (1914), 33-50. He left two notebooks; one, A, contains, pp 1-9, inscriptions copied and mostly already published, by Mendel; pp 39-47 transcriptions of 12 inscriptions from the Baths already published by Reinach; pp. 49-65 copies, by Boulanger, of 29 inscriptions discovered by Mendel in 1905; pp. 67-78 26 texts found in 1913, with the date of each find. B contains fair copies of the inscriptions found in 1905 and 1913, clearly prepared with a view to publication. We are very grateful to the late Madame Jeanne Robert for the gift of these notebooks. One text was published from these by B. Haussoullier, Revue de Philologie 44 (1920), 72-74. More texts were published from Boulanger's notebooks by L. Robert: Inscriptions grecques d'Asie Mineure. II. Inscription d'Aphrodisias, Anatolian Studies Buckler (Manchester, 1939), 227-48 (= L.Robert, Opera Minora Selecta, I-VII (Amsterdam 1969-1990) I, 611-32) and Épigrammes d'Aphrodisias in Hellenica 4, 127-135. Robert also cited others in:
Robert , Études Anatoliennes (Paris, 1937), 542 n. 2;
Robert , Hellenica 1 (Paris, 1940), 51; Inscriptions d'Aphrodisias, (1966), 394, n. 1, and 417.
